posts.name: Andy Gasser
posts.cooked:
I’m experimenting with publishing AprilTag data to AdvantageScope. I can publish the Pose3d objects, and they appear, but I can’t figure out how to publish the AprilTag objects (fiducial ID and Pose3d). The documentation says AprilTag is supported, but it doesn’t provide any details for how to do it.

This works for the Pose3d , but how do I set up the table to publish AprilTag objects instead of Pose3d objects?

posts.name: Andy Gasser
posts.cooked: AprilTag doesn’t have a static .struct field like Pose3d . Do I need to create my own struct or protobuf?

posts.name: Peter Johnson
posts.cooked: Whoops, you’re right, we haven’t implemented that in WPILib yet.  You could implement your own (either struct or protobuf) pretty easily, but I’m not sure what AdvantageScope is expecting here. @jonahb55 ?

posts.name: Andy Gasser
posts.cooked: Thanks. That’s what didn’t make sense to me. It says it’s “supported”, but it seems like they need to document what it expects since it doesn’t work out of the box.

posts.name: Jonah Bonner
posts.cooked: The expected format is based on this draft PR: [apriltag] Add initial Protobuf support to AprilTag by srimanachanta · Pull Request #5919 · wpilibsuite/allwpilib · GitHub . The only difference from what you posted is that it expects ID to be uppercase (I think it’s case sensitive?), which is consistent with how it appears in the AprilTag class and JSON format. Checking for lowercase “id” too would be a trivial change though.

posts.name: Peter Johnson
posts.cooked:
jonahb55:

The only difference from what you posted is that it expects ID to be uppercase (I think it’s case sensitive?)

Is AdvantageScope case sensitive?  It uses lowercase “id”: AdvantageScope/src/shared/geometry.ts at main · Mechanical-Advantage/AdvantageScope · GitHub

posts.name: Jonah Bonner
posts.cooked: That’s an internal data type. It expects the key used by the struct/protobuf to be uppercase “ID”: AdvantageScope/src/hub/tabControllers/ThreeDimensionController.ts at main · Mechanical-Advantage/AdvantageScope · GitHub
